problems: The JSON table describes per-class FID for AC-GAN with different initialization and iterations, while the LaTeX table compares FID/IW scores for generator/discriminator transfer configurations. The structures, metrics, and contexts are entirely different.
LaTeX 表格仅包含四列标题 '1M', '100K', '10K', '1K'，而 JSON 描述的是一个结构复杂、包含多级列名和数值数据的表格，两者在结构和内容上完全不匹配。

The JSON describes a table of symbols and their descriptions, while the LaTeX describes a table summarizing UCI datasets with numerical properties. The content, structure, and purpose are entirely different.

The JSON table has different column headers (42, 98, 140, 203) representing number of labeled nodes, while the LaTeX table has dataset names (DBLP, Pubmed, Cora co-authorship, Cora co-citation, Citeseer).; The JSON table reports results for varying |V_L| (labeled hypernodes), whereas the LaTeX table reports fixed results over 100 train-test splits without varying labeled node counts.; Numerical values differ significantly between the two tables; for example, CI on DBLP in LaTeX is 54.81±0.9, but in JSON it's 67.72±0.60 under '42' column.; The JSON table omits FastHyperGCN and includes only one row per method, while LaTeX includes multiple rows for H,X methods including FastHyperGCN.

The JSON table corresponds to a different experiment (Cora co-citation hypergraph with varying |V_L|) while the LaTeX table reports SSL experiments across multiple datasets (DBLP, Pubmed, Cora co-authorship/co-citation, Citeseer). The column headers and row structures are fundamentally different.

The JSON table is focused on Citeseer co-citation hypergraph with varying |V_L| values (42, 102, 138, 198), while the LaTeX table covers multiple datasets (DBLP, Pubmed, Cora, Citeseer) with fixed splits and no |V_L| variation.; Column headers in JSON ('42', '102', '138', '198') do not match any columns in LaTeX (which are dataset names like 'DBLP', 'Pubmed', etc.).; Row data in JSON corresponds to different experimental conditions (labelled node counts) not present in LaTeX.
